players.name: Nickson Kibabage
players.summary: Nickson Clement Kibabage is a Tanzanian professional footballer who plays as a Full-back for the Tanzania premier league club Young Africans S.C. and the Tanzania national team.

players.name: Ibrahim Hamad
players.summary: Ibrahim Abdallah Hamad, sometimes known as Ibrahim Bacca, is a Tanzanian professional footballer who plays as a centre-back for Young Africans. He has played for both the non-FIFA recognized Zanzibar national team, and for the recognized Tanzania national team.

players.name: Dickson Job
players.summary: Dickson Nickson Job is a Tanzanian professional footballer who plays as a centre-back for Tanzanian Premier League club Young Africans and the Tanzania national team.

players.name: Bakari Mwamnyeto
players.summary: Bakari Nondo Mwamnyeto is a Tanzanian professional footballer who plays as a centre-back for Tanzanian Premier League club Young Africans and the Tanzania national team.

players.name: Mohamed Husseini
players.summary: Mohamed Husseini Mohamed, also known as Zimbwe Jr, is a Tanzanian football player. He plays for Young Africans and the Tanzania national football team.

players.name: Lusajo Mwaikenda
players.summary: Lusajo Elukaga Mwaikenda is a Tanzanian professional footballer who plays as a centre-back for Tanzanian Premier League club Azam and the Tanzania national team.

players.name: Novatus Miroshi
players.summary: Novatus Dismas Miroshi is a Tanzanian professional footballer who plays as a left-back for Turkish side Göztepe and the Tanzania national team. Miroshi made his debut for the senior national team in 2021.

players.name: Shomari Kapombe
players.summary: Shomari Salum Kapombe is a Tanzanian professional footballer who plays as a right-back for Tanzanian Premier League club Simba and the Tanzania national team.

players.name: Feisal Salum
players.summary:
Feisal Salum Abdallah, commonly known as Fei Toto, is a Tanzanian professional footballer who plays as a Attacking midfielder for Tanzanian Premier League club
Azam FC and the Tanzania national team. He is a technically gifted and creative offensive playmaker who could play as an attacking midfielder or Box-to-box midfielder
 or as Deep-lying playmaker.

players.name: Charles M'Mombwa
players.summary: Kokola Charles William M'Mombwa is a professional footballer who plays as a midfielder for Maltese Premier League club Floriana. Born in the Democratic Republic of the Congo and raised in Tanzania and later Australia, he plays for the Tanzania national team.

players.name: Morice Abraham
players.summary: Morice Michael Abraham is a Tanzanian professional footballer who plays as a midfielder for Tanzanian Premier League club Simba and the Tanzania national team.

players.name: Haji Mnoga
players.summary: Haji Suleiman Haji Ali Mnoga is a professional footballer who plays as a right-back for EFL League Two side Salford City. Born in England, he plays for the Tanzania national team.

players.name: Tarryn Allarakhia
players.summary: Tarryn Allarakhia is a professional footballer who plays as a midfielder or a winger for National League side Rochdale. Born in England, he plays for the Tanzania national team.

players.name: Selemani Mwalimu
players.summary: Selemani Mwalimu Abdallah is a Tanzanian professional footballer who plays as a striker for Simba, on loan from Botola Pro club Wydad AC, and the Tanzania national team.

players.name: Mbwana Samatta
players.summary: Mbwana Ally Samatta is a Tanzanian professional footballer who plays as a striker for Ligue 1 club Le Havre, and captains the Tanzania national team.

players.name: Kibu Denis
players.summary: Kibu Denis Prosper, is a Tanzanian footballer who plays as a winger for Simba S.C., a club based in Dar es salaam.

players.name: Simon Msuva
players.summary: Simon Happygod Msuva is a Tanzanian professional footballer who plays as a forward for Iraq Stars League club Al-Talaba SC and the Tanzania national team.

players.name: Kelvin John
players.summary: Kelvin Pius John is a Tanzanian professional footballer who plays as a forward for Danish 1st Division side AaB and the Tanzania national team.
